cs.MR, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NA

The paper discusses the application of compressed sensing theory in magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), which is a subfield of medical imaging. Therefore, cs.MR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes new algorithms for compressed sensing reconstruction, which involves image processing and optimization techniques, making cs.CV and cs.IT likely sub-categories as well. The use of augmented Lagrangian methods and parallel processing also suggests cs.LG and cs.NA as possible sub-categories.
